IBADAN – Not less than 400 Yoruba Obas are expected to grace 2021 ‘Gathering of Kings To Praise The King of Kings’ festival. Briefing journalists In Ibadan, the National Pub­licity Secretary, Christian Traditional Rulers In Ni­geria, His Royal Majesty, Oba (Dr.) Festus Adekunle Adeyemi, the Alakola of Ikola-Ijesa, said the event has become an annual event following successful of two of its kind that was held in Osun State. He said the event is meant for both the Mus­lims, Christians and tradi­tional believer-monarchs, stressing that the testimo­nies received during the last two editions attracted many other monarchs, who had expressed willingness to join in this coming edi­tion. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Alakola maintained that the event had been an avenue for the traditional rulers to praise the Kings of Kings, who is the cre­ator of heaven and earth, stressing that through gen­uine worship and praise many of the monarchs in attendance would receive miracles and blessings in abundant. He disclosed that very soon they would be visiting the Olubadan of Ibadan­land, His Imperial Majesty, Oba Saliu Adetunji, to brief him on the event scheduled for January 23, 2021. Obasanjo Critical Voice In Politics, Says Udom As Ooni, Momoh, Others Eulogies Him AfCFTA Africa’s Only Path To Sustainable Development, ATPC Coordinator Convener of the event, Supreme Archbishop Em­manuel Ojo Olusegun Pow­erson, said the gathering had been very inspiring since inception. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION